methods.name: SetAlias<T>(T cacheable)
methods.summary: Sets an alias in the cache that will point to the specified ICacheable.
methods.remarks: This is used to have data available at multiple levels. For instance, if you had data cached under a parent, you could use this method to make an alias-reference to that nested data that would not be nested under a parent. This should only be used when the nested data has a globally unique id that is not reliant on its parent.

params.value: The type of ICacheable to make an alias for.
